---
description: Runtime boundaries and contract tests
alwaysApply: true
---

Runtime boundary rules:
- API layer handles transport concerns only.
- Domain/planner logic stays transport- and infrastructure-neutral.
- Runtime adapters (`rag`, `tabular`, provider clients) do not own user-facing copy.
- Debug payload assembly must use shared builders/helpers.

Mandatory tests when behavior changes:
- Routing tests.
- Fallback tests.
- Debug contract tests.
- Matching and schema-resolution tests.

Blocked patterns:
- Hardcoded domain-specific runtime field hints.
- Silent guessed column or table fallback.
- Expanding oversized mixed-responsibility files without extraction rationale.
